            <p>
                I have been learning as much as I can about Computer Science. First taking a .NET C# boot camp in Detroit, MI.
                After that I moved into a TA position at the boot camp where I studied. I have been working on open source projects, as well as personal projects, 
                so that I can keep pushing the limits of my knowledge. I have a full time position as a software engineer at Jato Dynamics in Detroit, 
                while also returning in the last to instruct a .NET CORE bootcamp at Grand Circus in the evenings, 
                and run multiple projects in my free time as well. Reach out for consultation or a possible business oppurtunity.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4 translucent-text-box">
        <div class="homePTag rounded">
            <h2>As a Musician</h2>
            <p>
                I have been a percussionist for 20 years. I played in Extreme Metal groups, Church groups, Rock groups, Jazz bands, and even
                Hip-Hop. I was not only a performing artist, but also a percussion instructor for 5 years. I taught from ages 6 and up,
                and learned a lot about patience and dedication during those years. I still practice and learn music almost daily, and would
                consider any contract gigs as a percusionist.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
